  "prompt": "When will Adobe XD be available for Windows?",
  "response": "Adobe XD has been available for Windows for several years. It was first released for Windows in December 2016, shortly after its initial release for macOS. Adobe XD is part of Adobe's suite of design tools and is used for designing and prototyping user experiences for web and mobile applications.\n\nIf you are looking to download Adobe XD for Windows, you can do so from the official Adobe website or through the Adobe Creative Cloud app. Keep in mind that Adobe XD is available both as a standalone purchase and as part of Adobe's Creative Cloud subscription service, which includes access to a wide range of Adobe's creative tools.\n\nAs of my last update in October 2023, Adobe XD continues to be supported and updated for both Windows and macOS. However, for the most current information, including any changes or updates to availability, it's always a good idea to check the official Adobe website or announcements from Adobe directly.",
